	<P><FONT FACE="Arial">The <I>Prasini Pteryga</I> (Green Wing) is an ecologist organization founded by members of the youth wing of the Golden Dawn. It uses a green flag, charged with a white Celtic Cross with outer white and inner green fimbriations.</P>

	<P><FONT FACE="Arial">A new flag appearing in 2010 has blue field and is charged with a smaller <I>maeandros</I> (meander) within a wreath, between the inscriptions <I>LAIKOS SYNDESMOS</I> (People's
Association) and <I>H RYSI AYGI</I> (Golden Dawn), possibly now the official name of the organization. 			
	<P><FONT FACE="Arial">Another Golden Dawn flag (Variant #5), using a combination of a football (soccer) club colors (orange and blue), is now used by some fans of the Apoel Football Club of Nicosia, Cyprus.  This is an example of how ultra-rightists attempt to infiltrate normal society, and by introducing their flag to football fans as a non-political symbol, it provides them with a valuable tool of later indoctrination.</P>
